[h2 id=StageOrdering 
	" Stage ordering
	$LF
]h2
[div class=p 
	"Since I'm not allowed to switch weapons, you might think that stage order doesn't matter. And broadly speaking, that is true... but there are some minutiae that can affect things.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" You get a different framerule for each stage depending on whether it's the first stage, subsequent to a short intermission, or subsequent to a long intermission.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" After you beat Bubbleman, there are straggling underwater lag frames at the start of the next stage, which messes with the framerule.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" After you beat Metalman, the conveyor belt affects you for 1 frame into the next stage.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"These are micro-optimizations that would've been impossible to reason about until I'd already completed all the stages. And some of the boss fights are so fiddly that these savings would
	$LF
	"probably get eaten anyway. As such, I chose to 
	[em 
		"ignore
	]em
	" them for this movie. Instead, I chose the order I did as an homage to 
	[a href=https://www.twitch.tv/videos/47049746 rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"ohon's run
	]a
	", which was the world record at the time I started on this project, and a true inspiration. Look how close it is to the current top runs despite the death and lack of major zips!
	$LF
]div
[h2 id=StageByStageNotes 
	" Stage by Stage Notes
	$LF
]h2
[h3 id=Wood 
	" Wood
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://i.imgur.com/hWMcIT9.gif 
	]img
	" 
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"It's just barely possible to kill this guy without jumping.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://i.imgur.com/YPrOz3P.gif 
	]img
	" 
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"The bats wake up based on RNG. If the middle bat happens to wake up, it can actually get you if you're doing frame perfect movement. You would have to jump slightly earlier and higher than necessary in order to lure it ever so slightly up and dodge it. Luckily, that didn't come up in this movie.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://i.imgur.com/FTHZe4L.png 
	]img
	" 
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Your X subpixel determines RNG. This ladder is a great spot to manipulate that because you always snap to the same coordinate but keep your subpixels when grabbing it. What am I manipulating RNG for here? The length of the fire snake. Things get real laggy real fast if you don't get the short one. There's also the issue of loot drops from the doggy, but that's a problem for future Cabin (1.5 seconds in the future).
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://i.imgur.com/5wQxZND.gif 
	]img
	" 
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Jumping against these guys actually makes it harder to shoot them. I do it for the sole purpose of slowing down without letting go of right. You can see I needed some quantum shots against all but the first monkey and bird.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://i.imgur.com/9XMn0Fr.gif 
	]img
	" 
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"These guys spawn based on your height and jump based on when they hit the ground. I wouldn't be able to jump over them if I didn't manipulate them with a few well-timed 1-frame jumps.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://i.imgur.com/edUjB6V.png 
	]img
	" 
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"While it may look like I'm carefully timing shots between the leaves of Woodman's shield, the shield is in fact a solid square hitbox. It's just a matter of hitbox overlap priority (Woodman himself is not invincible). There's a ~4 pixel window where this works 100% of the time, and a ~2 pixel window where it works 50% of the time because the lemon exists for 1 frame overlapping the shield but not the boss (quantum shots be like). In fact, 
	[a href=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ES5BEaglXBo rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Crash bombs can even penetrate from a distance
	]a
	".
	$LF
]div
